1
00:00:00,750 --> 00:00:06,166
One night, a shell fell on the building,
it shook a little from the impact

2
00:00:08,208 --> 00:00:12,666
You probably will not believe this,
will not believe what I am about to say

3
00:00:13,000 --> 00:00:17,791
I said, salvation has come, I felt relieved,
maybe we die, it was a relief for us

4
00:00:17,791 --> 00:00:21,625
Either we die and find rest,
or we get out

5
00:00:23,083 --> 00:00:29,375
There was a small commotion among them,
and movement outside, that night they did not take anyone for interrogation

6
00:00:31,083 --> 00:00:35,833
The next day, around 12:30,
or after the noon prayer

7
00:00:35,916 --> 00:00:38,833
Let us be precise,
right after the noon prayer

8
00:00:39,041 --> 00:00:42,208
They executed someone,
they took someone, I heard them take him

9
00:00:43,041 --> 00:00:48,250
They were even mocking him,
they said, this one is gone, God be with him

10
00:00:49,250 --> 00:00:52,791
And said mocking words
that I do not want to repeat

11
00:00:53,416 --> 00:00:57,125
A person who passed away, may God have mercy on him,
they killed him in the open

12
00:00:57,750 --> 00:01:03,333
When they came back, we had prayed noon prayer,
and the prison was shelled

13
00:01:03,458 --> 00:01:09,875
My room was filled with dust,
and there were sounds and chaos outside, unimaginable

14
00:01:10,625 --> 00:01:15,958
I hear screaming, and nobody moves,
he says we have orders

15
00:01:16,250 --> 00:01:20,166
Any of you who tries to make any unusual movement,
we will kill you immediately

16
00:01:21,500 --> 00:01:26,041
Of course, when did I realize my room was the last one?
Because I was the last person to be taken out

17
00:01:27,250 --> 00:01:32,791
The guard came, rather Abu Abdullah
the interrogator himself, he is the one who came

18
00:01:33,083 --> 00:01:39,791
Abu Abdullah came and took me, stood me at the door,
blindfolded me, and placed a laptop in my hands

19
00:01:39,833 --> 00:01:45,041
He said, carry this, held my hand,
and said, walk with me, I will guide you

20
00:01:45,291 --> 00:01:51,791
When I tell you to step, you step,
we went up, I think from here, and we walked

21
00:01:51,791 --> 00:01:58,625
I do not know, I was blindfolded,
this place, because there was chaos and unimaginable dust, we were suffocating

22
00:01:59,500 --> 00:02:03,708
We walked, kept walking until I felt
we went down a little and there was dirt

23
00:02:04,708 --> 00:02:12,125
Here he removed my blindfold, and in front of me
were about 14 or 15 people, I do not remember the exact number

24
00:02:12,541 --> 00:02:17,291
Because after that moment,
I was in shock for two days

25
00:02:18,166 --> 00:02:22,250
There was a person who had been killed,
they killed him before I came out

26
00:02:23,625 --> 00:02:26,541
A killed person, before I came out
they had already killed him

27
00:02:26,708 --> 00:02:29,541
The ones who were taken out before me
saw how they killed him

28
00:02:31,125 --> 00:02:36,666
We were all like this in this position,
and like this, and nobody made any movement

29
00:02:36,708 --> 00:02:44,125
He said, any unusual movement and we will kill you,
even if you step out of line, they lined us up like a column

30
00:02:44,750 --> 00:02:50,666
At that moment, I remembered Camp Speicher,
how they executed them and lined them up like this, I said it is over, they will execute us

31
00:02:51,083 --> 00:02:55,583
Here I felt relieved, I said,
this is enough, death is more merciful than this

32
00:02:57,125 --> 00:03:01,583
We walked, the number of guards increased here,
there were many of them

33
00:03:02,291 --> 00:03:07,833
They surrounded us from everywhere, and I was the last one,
he kept hitting me with his rifle, saying nobody moves

34
00:03:09,125 --> 00:03:17,125
They shouted at someone named Abdul Sattar
or Abdul Jabbar, I do not remember, he told him, any movement and I will kill you

35
00:03:18,041 --> 00:03:24,291
We walked a little through the tunnel,
until we came out facing this building on the other side

36
00:03:25,166 --> 00:03:29,083
We entered a building, then exited it
to an open area, the vehicles arrived of course

37
00:03:29,458 --> 00:03:35,541
When we reached the building, we exited the tunnel
via stairs into an unfinished building, still on its frame

38
00:03:36,458 --> 00:03:43,625
They grabbed a person, dragged him to the side and shot
him on the spot, he said nobody look, this one had a death sentence, he said do not be afraid

39
00:03:44,333 --> 00:03:46,833
The one who said that was Abu Abdullah,
the interrogator

40
00:03:47,541 --> 00:03:54,541
The one who executed him looked visibly delighted,
and the other one said to him, how lucky you are

41
00:03:55,541 --> 00:04:03,166
As if he envied him for this moment,
I wished this one would not catch us, so he would not gloat over us

42
00:04:03,208 --> 00:04:07,416
So he would not feel this thrill,
I do not know where he got it from

43
00:04:08,250 --> 00:04:13,041
Vehicles arrived, they took us and ordered us
all into one van

44
00:04:13,416 --> 00:04:18,166
The rest of the members
rode in another van

45
00:04:18,500 --> 00:04:25,458
Abu Abdullah rode behind us on a motorcycle,
carrying his pistol

46
00:04:26,375 --> 00:04:32,708
He looked at us, and whenever we looked,
he signaled us not to look, you must not know where we are going

47
00:04:33,833 --> 00:04:38,791
We entered the room,
they took us somewhere, a location in Tabqa

48
00:04:39,500 --> 00:04:44,166
We entered, the car drove inside,
a large gate, and the car went into the yard

49
00:04:44,375 --> 00:04:48,125
We entered a room, and for the first time,
all prisoners sat together

50
00:04:49,208 --> 00:04:53,208
We sat down, and the people I knew from Tabqa
sat beside me

51
00:04:54,625 --> 00:04:57,583
We talked a little,
exchanged greetings and spoke

52
00:04:58,208 --> 00:05:04,958
One of the prisoners was drinking tea,
someone said to him, do you really want to drink tea right now, in this situation?

53
00:05:05,000 --> 00:05:08,291
That person was clearly tense,
he said, my death sentence has been issued

54
00:05:09,291 --> 00:05:15,958
So let me live in the moment, let me enjoy,
we have not even had tea in days

55
00:05:17,291 --> 00:05:24,083
After that, they divided us into two groups,
some were taken like me, along with other people

56
00:05:24,333 --> 00:05:28,375
They took us and placed us in a holding facility
belonging to the Islamic Police

57
00:05:29,375 --> 00:05:33,875
And they went with the others,
those who also had prisoners in the same building, they put them together

58
00:05:34,541 --> 00:05:41,166
The rest were all taken to Raqqa, some had to attend
closed courses, or served out their sentences there

59
00:05:41,333 --> 00:05:46,708
Some were executed, some survived
and returned to Tabqa, and we met them

60
00:05:47,458 --> 00:05:54,208
Interviewer: Can you name the people you remember,
whether those who stayed with you in Tabqa or those who went to Raqqa?

61
00:05:55,291 --> 00:06:00,958
I do not know them, I only know,
I only know three from Tabqa

62
00:06:01,791 --> 00:06:06,875
I know two of them to this day,
and they are still afraid, I prefer not to mention their names

63
00:06:07,083 --> 00:06:12,875
Because I know them, it is not possible,
to this day they live in real terror

64
00:06:13,875 --> 00:06:20,041
There was a person named Abboud al-Shawwakh,
I know him, he was brought in and left with us through the tunnel

65
00:06:21,750 --> 00:06:26,416
He is the only person from Tabqa I remember,
the other two I prefer not to name

66
00:06:27,333 --> 00:06:30,916
Most of the prisoners' charges were apostasy
and collaboration

67
00:06:31,041 --> 00:06:36,666
In their language, apostasy means
anyone who was a collaborator

68
00:06:37,791 --> 00:06:45,500
Or for example anyone they considered an infidel,
collaboration meant anyone who had ties with any faction outside their control

69
00:06:46,083 --> 00:06:51,250
They would charge them, sometimes the charges
were over trivial things, even a photo

70
00:06:51,333 --> 00:06:55,708
For example, if you had a photo of the Free Syrian Army,
that was considered collaboration

71
00:06:56,041 --> 00:07:04,291
Sometimes, even a photo of the Syrian flag
was considered collaboration, they treated it as collaboration
